reviewText: I do not recommend taking this type of course, take one and pass it, however after a few days I have tried to review the material, and my surprise is that it asks me to pay again to be able to review the material. Of course coursera gives me a small discount for having already paid it previously.
poor audio, system hard to work with but the content is good
It's more of a beginner course than a intermediate course.
Not good enough. Need more visualization technique.
That was very interesting and eye-openning
Short precise intro to data visualization with Python. The lecturer's competency is high, I'd prefer a bit more motivation from him.
Good for beginners to learn data visualization. Not recommended for people already heard the word(Just see their official website about scatter plot, joint plot and heat map).
session needs to be extended for a longer time,It was a good experience..:)

Excellent course !  Looking forward to learn more
i'm very satisfied with this guide, the explanation is on point.
Great content just the examples are not not enough maybe more examples need to be provided.
Great project to get started with data visualization.
Simple short and easy project. Someone with basic knowledge of python can also learn a lot.
it is really a short and excellent course for beginners
Good and fast course/project, you'll learn a lot in an hour, if you already know basics of python.
It is a brilliant introductory course for someone who is just beginning to learn using pandas and matplotlib.

Excellent course for a beginner who have a basic idea of Python and dont know anything about Data Visualization. Excellent course Join it You Will not regret. And lastly, thank you Professor for such an effective teaching.
